{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01CmbXnDZ4Ncche24jwk5jhc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TbuxyDgPi7sgP7F4kSmoPt","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Salmon Teriyaki.generated.24.txt","content":"SALMON TERIAKI\n\nServes 4 | Main course | Prep: 1O mins | Coo ķ: 15 mins\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n\n4 salmon fillets (150g each)\n1/2 cup soy sauce (sôy)\n3 tbsp mirlln\n2 tbsp sake (or dry sherry)\n1 tbsp sugar\n3 cloves garlic, grated\n1 tbsp ginger, grated (ırUzer)\n2 tbsp sesame oil\n1 tsp cornstarcḧ\n2 tbsp water\nSesame seeds for garnish\nSpring onions, chopped\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Make teriyaki sauce: Combine soy sauce, mirin, sake, sugar, garlic,\nand ginger in a small saucepan.\n\n2. Bring to simmer over medium heat. Mix cornstarch with water and stir\ninto sauce.\n\n3. Simmer for 5 minutes until sauce thickens. Remove from heat and stir\nin sesame oil.\n\n4. Pat salmon dry with pàper towe1s. Season lightly with salt and pepper.\n\n5. Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Add oil and sear salmon, skin-\nside down, for 4-5 minutes.\n\n6. Flip and cook for another 3 minutes. Brush gener0usly with teriyaki\nsauce.\n\n7. Cook for 1-2 minutes more, basting with sauce.\n\n8. Garnish with sesame seeds and spring onions.\n\n9. Serve immediately with steamed rice or vegetables.\n\nNUTRITION TIP:\n\nSalmon is rich in omega-3 fatty acids. Teriyaki glaze complements the\nfish's natural flavors perfectly.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":88750,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":88750},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"00f57389-774e-4c2a-a17b-8f302bef767c","uuid":"6e8f1e8e-de74-4ae8-919a-10ac93c7ad4a"}
