{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QsDEpvk1BnUW4Ty15zvoPK","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lentil Vegetable Soup.generated.24.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"00f57389-774e-4c2a-a17b-8f302bef767c","uuid":"1a42e541-b358-4e04-9a73-f39a16e8a000","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lentil Vegetable Soup.generated.24.txt","content":"LENTIL\nVEGETABLE\nSOUP\n\nServes 6 | Lunch/Dinner | Vegan | Prep: 10 mins | Cook: 35 mins\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n\n250g red lentils, rinsed\n2L vegetable stock\n2 medium carrots, diced\n2 celery stalks, diced\n1 medium onion, finely chopped\n3 cloves garlic, minced\n1 can (400g) diced tomatoes\n2 tbsp olive oil\n1 tsp cumin\n1 tsp paprika\n1/2 tsp turmeric\n2 bay leaves\nSalt and pepper to taste\nFresh cilantro or parsley\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Heat olive oil in large pot. Sauté onion, garlic, carrots, and celery\nuntil softened, about 5 minutes.\n\n2. Add spices: cumin, paprika, and turmeric. Stir constantly for\n30 seconds until fragrant.\n\n3. Pour in lentils, vegetable stock, tomatoes, and bay leaves.\n\n4. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 25-30 minutes until\nlentils are tender and starting to break down.\n\n5. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n6. Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro or parsley.\n\nVARIATIONS:\n\nAdd spinach, kale, or diced sweet potato for more nutrition and flavor.\nSwap red lentils for green or brown for heartier texture.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
